# UI Framework: Spartan UI + Tailwind CSS

## Stack
- **Components**: Spartan UI (headless, Angular CDK-based)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS (utility-first)
- **Behavior**: Angular CDK (drag-drop, overlays, a11y, virtual scroll)
- **NO Angular Material** — do not install or import @angular/material

## Spartan UI Patterns
- Import brain (behavior) and helm (UI) separately:
  `import { BrnTableModule } from '@spartan-ng/brain/table';`
  `import { HlmTableModule } from '@spartan-ng/ui-table-helm';`
- Brain = logic/a11y, Helm = styled component
- Components are copied into the project (full ownership)

## Tailwind Conventions
- Mobile-first: write base styles for mobile, override with sm:/md:/lg:/xl:
- Use colla-theming CSS variables via Tailwind config:
  `bg-colla-primary`, `text-colla-secondary`, etc.
- No hardcoded colors for branding — always use CSS custom properties
- Minimum touch target: `min-h-11 min-w-11` (44px) on interactive elements in mobile

## Responsive Requirements
- Sidebar: hidden <lg, visible ≥lg. Mobile uses Sheet (slide-over)
- Tables: full table ≥lg, card layout <lg
- Forms: single column <md, multi-column ≥md
- All layouts must be tested at 320px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px

## Component Structure

```typescript
@Component({
  standalone: true,
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
  imports: [BrnTableModule, HlmTableModule],
  host: { class: 'block' }, // Tailwind needs block display
})
```
